result.execSummary:
The defendant Camille J. Hillary was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Camille J. Hillary in court with attorney Aneeq Ahmad.  Haley Jo Johnson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minutes filed.
Order Denying Defendant's Motion to Suppress

9:02 a.m.  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  
Haley Jo Johnson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant Guy S Hillary in court with attorney Aneeq Ahmad.  
Also present in Court is Defendant Camille J. Hillary.  
Matter is before the Court on the Defendant's Motion Suppress Evidence from the Subpoena.  
Court wants to first address the Franks Motion.  
Court takes short recess while we wait for State's first witness to return to courtroom.  
9:06 a.m.  Deputy Daniel Winger is sworn and testifies on direct exam of Attorney Rea.  

Exhibit 1 marked and identifed as Intelligence Report.  
Exhibit 1 is offered and received.  

9:14 a.m.  Cross exam by Attorney Ahmad.  
9:23 a.m.  Response by Deputy Winger to Court's questions.  
9:26 a.m.  Follow up questions of Deputy Winger by Attorney Johnson.  
9:27 a.m.  Recross by Attorney Ahmad.  

9:30 a.m.  Court hears argument of Attorneys.  
9:30 a.m.  Argument by Attorney Ahmad.  He agrees that he can make no argument that it was deliberate or reckless or a disregard for the truth
9:32 a.m.  Court makes findings and denies the Franks Motion.

9:33 a.m.  Response by Deputy Winger to Court's question as to Alliant Energy matter.  
9:34 a.m.  Attorney Johnson has no further questions
9:34 a.m.  Cross exam by Attorney Ahmad.  
9:35 a.m.  Attorney Johnson has no further follow up.  

9:36 a.m.  Court did review briefs submitted by the parties.  Court does not believe US vs. Miller is on point.  
9:37 a.m.  Discussion between Court and Attorneys concerning whether the Independent source doctrine applies in this case.  
Court does not believe that the independent source document applies.  
Next issue is whether utility records have a reasonable expectation of privacy.  
Discussion between Court and Attorneys.  
Response by Deputy Winger to Court's questions as to whether the information can be accessed on line.  
9:45 a.m.  Argument by Attorneys Ahmad and Johnson.  Continued discussion between Court and Attorneys.  
9:50 a.m.  Response by Deputy Winger to Court's questions.  
9:51 a.m.  Continued argument by Attorneys.  
9:59 a.m.  Court makes findings.  Court believes that information readily available to the public would have been sufficient to issue the search warrant.  
The summary provided by Mr. Hale in paragraph "J" ties it all together and there are sufficent indicia of reliability.  
Court denies the Motion for reasons set forth on the record.  
10:00 a.m.  Response by Attorney Ahmad.  Court believes utitlity records are different than bank records.  
10:01 a.m.  Attorney Rea asks if this decides the Motion in the co-defendant's case.  Attorney Ahmad confirms that it does.  

10:02 a.m.  Discussion concerning further scheduling of both cases.  
Cases are not currently joined for trial.  Attorney Johnson will file a motion.  
Attorney Ahmad would first need to speak with his clients before agreeing to joinder.  
State to file Motion for joinder to be filed by January 22nd.  
Motion to Join scheduled for:  February 16, 2016 at 10:00 a.m.
Final pre-trial scheduled for:  May 25, 2016 at 2:30 p.m.
Jury Trial scheduled for:  May 31 and June 1, 2016 at 8:30 a.m. 
If cases are NOT joined, parties agree that Mr. Hillary's case will be tried first.  
10:06 a.m.  Court in recess.
